com.antigenomics.alisa.algebra.matrix

Class SparseVector

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.antigenomics.alisa.algebra.matrix.Vector
      • com.antigenomics.alisa.algebra.matrix.SparseVector
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Container<IndexedVectorValue,Vector>, ImmutableLinearSpaceObject<Vector>, LinearSpaceObject<Vector>, TypedCloneable<Vector>, VectorSpace<Vector,Matrix>, Encoding, Representation, Serializable, Iterable<IndexedVectorValue>

    public class SparseVector
extends Vector
    A one-dimensional vector backed by a sparse storage (list of indexed values). One should work with this object as an iterable of IndexedVectorElement to achieve maximum performance. Calling getAt method is slow as it requires iterating over the list of indexed values. Sparse vector extends mutable linear object and can be scaled/added with vectors of the same length. It also extends a vector space object and can be used in scalar and outer product with other vectors, as well as linear, bilinear and symmetric bilinear forms with matrices.
